    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf a large JSON string is incomplete the Error `E1510: Value too large` will be thrown instead of `E474: Unexpected end of input`. This causes problems in plugins which try to catch a decoding error, but then miss this one case. It happens for example in https://github.com/monkoose/nvlime/issues/12 where Neovim is expected to receive very large messages in JSON format from a running Lisp process.\r\n\r\nFrom my limited investigation it looks like error happens in `vim_vsnprintf_typval` because the logic falls into `format_overflow_error` while parsing the format directive `%.*s`, but I was not able to understand how the variable `j` is computed (`src/nvim/strings.c:1616` in Neovim 0.10.1). \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nTake these two large JSON files:\r\n\r\n- [buffered.json](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/16403776/buffered.json)\r\n- [buffered-incomplete.json](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/16403777/buffered-incomplete.json) (missing the closing `]` at the end)\r\n\r\nLet's try to read both of them in and parse them.\r\n\r\n```vim\r\nlet complete = readfile('buffered.json')\r\nlet incomplete = readfile('buffered-incomplete.json')\r\n\r\n\" This works fine:\r\necho json_decode(complete[0])\r\n\r\n\" This trows E1510\r\necho json_decode(incomplete[0])\r\n\r\n\" This throws E474\r\necho json_decode('[1, 3, 4')\r\n```\r\n\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe error thrown for an incomplete JSON string should be the same for all string sizes.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, Vim 9.1 raises `E491` and partially decodes the string\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nVoid Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.13.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nVoid package",
