            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "A possible solution is to just to `vsnprintf()` instead of `vim_vsnprintf()`:\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/message.c b/src/nvim/message.c\r\nindex 73712489ad..3543f427b9 100644\r\n--- a/src/nvim/message.c\r\n+++ b/src/nvim/message.c\r\n@@ -818,7 +818,7 @@ static bool semsgv(const char *fmt, va_list ap)\r\n     return true;\r\n   }\r\n \r\n-  vim_vsnprintf(errbuf, sizeof(errbuf), fmt, ap);\r\n+  vsnprintf(errbuf, sizeof(errbuf), fmt, ap);\r\n \r\n   return emsg(errbuf);\r\n }\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, this will cause problems if translations use features in `vim_vsnprintf()` that are not present in `vsnprintf()` for some compilers. E.g. from the documentation of MSVC (and as mentioned in vim/vim#10577), it seems that the `vsnprintf()` it provides doesn't support positional arguments.",
